# 1️⃣ `struct` vs `class`

Before understanding OOP, first understand this:

👉 Programs deal with **real-world entities**.

Examples:

* Student
* Car
* Bank Account

Each entity has:

* data
* behavior

---

# Problem Before OOP

Imagine storing student data:

```cpp id="5gaw6s"
string name1;
int age1;
float marks1;

string name2;
int age2;
float marks2;
```

Messy ❌

Hard to manage.

---

# Solution → Group Related Data

That’s why `struct` and `class` exist.

---

# Part A — Structure (`struct`)

---

## Simple Idea

👉 `struct` groups related data together.

---

## Real-World Example

Think of a student form:

```text id="jlwmw5"
Name
Age
Marks
```

All belong to ONE student.

---

## Example

```cpp id="9a9a7x"
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

struct Student
{
    string name;
    int age;
    float marks;
};

int main()
{
    Student s1;

    s1.name = "Akshay";
    s1.age = 20;
    s1.marks = 85.5;

    cout << s1.name;
}
```

---

# What Actually Happens

`Student` becomes a custom data type.

Like:

```cpp id="o9lk3u"
int
float
char
```

Now additionally:

```cpp id="5ph2cy"
Student
```

---

# Mental Model

```text id="v20xyc"
struct = blueprint for related data
```

---

# Why Struct Exists

Instead of separate variables:

```text id="ns2rqq"
name, age, marks
```

We create ONE logical unit:

```text id="ukq1r0"
Student
```

---

# Part B — Class (`class`)

Now comes the powerful version.

---

## Simple Idea

👉 Class = data + functions together

---

## Real-World Example

Think of a car:

### Data:

```text id="zq8zqv"
speed
color
fuel
```

### Functions:

```text id="qymf4f"
start()
brake()
accelerate()
```

---

# Example

```cpp id="1j3k44"
class Car
{
public:

    string color;

    void start()
    {
        cout << "Car Started";
    }
};
```

---

# What Makes Class Powerful?

Now data and behavior stay together.

This is how real-world systems are built.

---

# Main Difference: `struct` vs `class`

| struct               | class             |
| -------------------- | ----------------- |
| default public       | default private   |
| mainly data grouping | full OOP features |
| simpler              | more secure       |

---

# IMPORTANT 🔥

In C++:

```text id="x7q6ur"
struct and class are almost same
```

Only default access changes.

---

# Mental Model (Never Forget)

```text id="m25ru2"
struct → simple container
class → smart object
```

---

# Connection to Real Life

Everything around you is an object:

* phone
* bike
* ATM

Each has:

* properties
* actions

That’s exactly OOP.

